khtiyani, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cA man will not hit the mark, nor fulfill his manhood, until he has two characteristics: Forgiving people and overlooking their faults.\u201d Source: al-Muru\u0304\u2019ah 106 \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0639\u064e\u0628\u0652\u062f\u0650 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0651\u064e\u0647\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0634\u064f\u0645\u064e\u064a\u0652\u0637\u0650 \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e \u0623\u064e\u064a\u0651\u064f\u0648\u0628 \u0627\u0644\u0633\u0651\u064e\u062e\u0652\u062a\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0627\u0646\u0650\u064a \u0631\u062d\u0645\u0647 \u0627\u0644\u0644\u0647 \u0644\u064e\u0627\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":24242,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/01\/04\/umar-ii-rifq-dunya-akhirah\/","url_meta":{"origin":24291,"position":1},"title":"Umar II on Kindness: None is kind but that Allah will be kind to him","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"January 4, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Hibban reported: Umar ibn Abdul Aziz, may Allah have mercy on him, said, \u201cThe most beloved matters to Allah are three: forgiveness in a position of power, moderation in a position of affluence, and gentleness in worship. No one is kind to another in this world but that Allah\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":905,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2011\/07\/06\/umar-mercy-pardon-forgiveness\/","url_meta":{"origin":24291,"position":2},"title":"Umar on Forgiveness: No mercy for the unmerciful, unforgiving","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 6, 2011","format":false,"excerpt":"Qabisah ibn Jabir reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \"Whoever does not show mercy will not receive mercy. Whoever does not forgive others will not be forgiven. Whoever does not pardon others will not be pardoned. Whoever does not protect others will not be protected.\"\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":22390,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2016\/04\/01\/pardon-tazir-hudud\/","url_meta":{"origin":24291,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Ta&#8217;zir: Pardon criminal punishments if possible, except hudud","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 1, 2016","format":false,"excerpt":"Ibn Umar reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cWaive the punishments with magnanimity, for that is part of righteousness.\u201d In another narration, the Prophet said, \u201cExcept for those regarding the limits (h\u0323udud) of Allah.\u201d Source: Maka\u0304rim al-Akhla\u0304q lil-T\u0323abara\u0304ni\u0304 62 Grade: Sahih (authentic) according to\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":31836,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/06\/08\/dua-ask-afwa-afiyah-akhirah\/","url_meta":{"origin":24291,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Dua: Ask Allah for pardon and wellness","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 8, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cAsk your Lord for forgiveness and wellness in the world and the Hereafter. If you are given forgiveness and wellness in the world and the Hereafter, you have succeeded.\u201d Source: Sunan Ibn Ma\u0304jah 3848 Grade:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Faith \u0627\u0644\u0627\u064a\u0645\u0627\u0646","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/faith-iman\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":2873,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2012\/04\/12\/prophet-always-recommends-forgiveness\/","url_meta":{"origin":24291,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Pardon: The Prophet always recommended forgiveness","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"April 12, 2012","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: I never saw a case involving legal retaliation being referred to the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, but that he would command pardoning the criminal. Source: Sunan Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 4497 Source:\u00a0Sahih\u00a0(authentic) according to Al-Albani \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652 \u0623\u064e\u0646\u064e\u0633\u0650 \u0628\u0652\u0646\u0650 \u0645\u064e\u0627\u0644\u0650\u0643\u064d \u0642\u064e\u0627\u0644\u064e\u00a0\u0645\u064e\u0627 \u0631\u064e\u0623\u064e\u064a\u0652\u062a\u064f \u0627\u0644\u0646\u064e\u0651\u0628\u0650\u064a\u064e\u0651 \u0635\u064e\u0644\u064e\u0651\u0649\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_te